Take off the top and enjoy some real summer driving.

1967 Olds Oldsmobile 442 W30 So cool a must see............ odometer: 32086 1967 Stunning Rare car A 1967 Oldsmobile 2 door sedan 442 W-30 Cutlass ---------------------------------------------------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------------- Early history information regarding my  Black on Black Beauty! 1967 Oldsmobile 442-W31 SN338077M279104.  To whom it may concern.  This vehicle was specially built for Richard E Haas to campaign in major NHRA drag racing events in 1967. It was important to Oldsmobile， that they had good representation at all regional and national events in an effort to win the NHRA manufacturer's championship.  Oldsmobile won several back-to-back stock car manufacturer's championships during this era.  Dale Smith“Oldsmobile Special Vehicle Operations Manager" was very successful in working with the sanctioning bodies and all types of racers. Dale was able to get a large return for a very small investment(Oldsmobile had no racing budget at this time); Dale was limited to giving a few parts and information to those who chose to run Oldsmobile vehicles.  I worked at the GM Proving Grounds for Oldsmobile， and in1965 ran a 442 automatic. In 1966 I ran a four-speed tri-power and got a little engine help from Mr. Smith. As a GM employee，, I could order and buy a new vehicle equipped， as I wanted at a GM discount. l also had the option of purchasing a vehicle with 3000 miles on it for a larger discount. In 1967 I told Mr.Smith that I would like to run all of the regional and National NHRA events and wanted to know if he could help in any way?  We ordered the above vehicle equipped, as we wanted. On the build date, Mr. Smith made sure the folks that installed the insulation did not work too hard, in fact, Dale most likely took them to the pop machine as the car passed by.  The vehicle was sent to the Proving Ground to get its 3000 miles. Meanwhile, Mr. Smith was at Olds Engineering Assembly Dept having an NHRA legal blueprinted engine built. He did not stop there, he got with the transmission group and they came up with a super combination and special torque converters with a manual switch to be mounted on the floorboard to operate the pitch or the ratio of the converter at will. Later in the year the transmission group built and let us run a six-speed in this car.  At the end of the 3000 miles, the vehicle was sent to Olds engineering where the engine, transmission, and suspension parts were installed.  I picked up the vehicle from product delivery like any other 3000-mile car and ran all of the NHRA events, including the Nationals at Indy.  At the end of 1967, I sold the above vehicle. Had two more owners and I purchased the vehicle. Have all owner info!  I was fortunate to be able to work at the GM proving grounds for Oldsmobile during this time frame. I did most of the performance testing for Oldsmobile including, the cold air induction that is a production, feature on the above car. It was nice to be apart of the test and development. Competing was even better.  For anyone interested in Oldsmobile history, a book by Dale Smith is available and published by Backfire press PO Box 455 Harrison MI. 49625  (Racing to the past: Oldsmobile and its demise/D. Dale Smith-Harrison, MI; Backfire press,2004.  Regards  Richard E Haas   This car is in South Fenton, Michigan  This car has an asking price of US funds 112,900.00 US dollars cash or wire transfer

It's really hard to sell this vehicle after putting so much time and upgrades into her over the last 5 years, but I'm no longer working as a field biologist and so it's time to let her go. I'm the third owner and have logged 125,000 of the 168,000 miles; mostly highway miles but also putting the vehicle through the paces off-road. This is an amazingly capable off-road rig and by far the best (and most fun) vehicle I've ever owned. I've taken great care of her and done all scheduled and necessary maintenance, mostly at the local Toyota dealership.   This is the rare 2010 sandstone color (including the roof) Trail Teams Edition FJ Cruiser which in addition to Toyota's standard Off Road Package includes: Bilstein shocks, rear differential lock, A-TRAC, front and rear skid plates, TRD beadlock-style alloy wheels, BFG tires, rock rails, hood blackout color to reduce glare, wheel locks, subwoofer and built-in inverter providing 12V, 100W and 115V 400W outlets.   I've added upgrades and modifications to create a true overland adventure vehicle, including: ARB 47L fridge/freezer mounted on slider drawer, dash-mounted solar controller and battery isolater for portable or permanent solar panel charging (pv panels not included; I was using a fold-up/portable solar array), Rhino Rack Pioneer Platform roof rack, James Baroud Space Evo rooftop tent, Rhino Rack Foxwing wrap-around awning and simple platform build for efficient gear storage in back.   The one and only repair needed is that the volume dial on the stereo doesn't work, but you can still control volume via the steering wheel controls.  Asking $28,000 or best offer and happy to answer any questions

For sale or trade: 1995 Land Cruiser 80 series — Triple Locked, Lifted, and LS swapped  The pandemic has changed many things, least of which our home, our jobs, and how we spend our time, which is including some construction projects where we need a true truck more than this beautiful 80 series.   Unfortunately, that means our beautiful leather-lined, LS-swapped 80 series needs a new home. We hope to not be selling outright with no trade, and are hoping someone has one or more of the following they no longer need, and need or want an 80 series, triple locked from the factory, with LS swap. However, we realize how difficult some of these items are to get and that you may only have cash, hence the cash price listed.  Price is 35k USD picked up in the Methow Valley. We really prefer local pickup in the Methow Valley. If you haven’t been, it is one of the more unique mountain towns.   However, if you would like delivered, we can deliver within AZ, NV, NM, CO, or UT for $1500. Any further and you’ll most likely need to arrange your own delivery.   If no one on here wants in the next few weeks, we plan to put on BringATrailer, but the end price will likely be higher. Wanted to open it up to real drivers on here first before it goes and sits in a 18 car garage to have wine spilt on it.   We prefer trades (plus cash on either end depending on what you’ve got) for the following: - Scamp or Casita or Airstream Bambi or Argosy trailer under 19’ - 1998 or later automatic Tacoma or Tundra 4x4 xtra or crew cab or T100 of similar vintage (or maybe a Nissan Frontier) - preferably with at least a 6’ bed - A newer daily driver Subaru Outback, Forester 2001 or later (or maybe a Toyota 4Runner) - Small or Medium 29er or 27.5” Hardtail or Full Suspension mountain or gravel bike(s), newer, prefer 1x11 or 1x12 drivetrain - NRS, Sol, or Hala paddle boards > 8 feet - Modern modular cabin / home or wood yurt 250 - 750 square feet (or a WA licensed contractor to build on site) - must meet current building code - Patented mining claim in Colorado, mountain land in Washington near Leavenworth, Winthrop, or similar, or land near Sun Valley or Driggs Idaho or Salt Lake City or Park City Utah  Land Cruiser has had a Western life (Texas, Washington) life. Many years of maintenance and upgrade paperwork available on paper and digitally. $45,000 + in documented work over past ~ 5 years   This is a 95 with stock: - Triple lockers (front, rear, center) - Luxury interior - leather and tortoise-looking stuff  - 3rd row seats  Extras: - ARB front bumper and Warn VR-S series winch (synthetic line) - $2100 installed - Custom diamond plate rear bumper with hitch, tire swing out, and 4-pin wiring harness - $1800 installed - Sliders - $600 installed  - 3” OME lift all around - $1575+ installed - Newer (5k miles) ~33” BFG KM3 tires ($1400 installed) on powder coated steel FJ rims  - LS swap engine 5.3L and 4L60e transmission (professionally done by The Land Cruiser Shop) - donor low-miles engine and rebuilt transmission. If you aren’t familiar with The Land Cruiser Shop, they are one of the top Land Cruiser shops in the West, and this work was beautiful (and pricey @ $25000). Includes emissions components. - Digital gauges that actually work and change colors for day / night driving - Newer ball joints and u joint - Newer front leather upholstery ($940 installed)  - Newer brakes ($450) - Newer AC w new compressor, condenser, and valves ($2000) - Newer fuel tank, fuel pump and lines ($950) - Full-sized spare  - Rebuilt birfields and replaced front drive shaft and u-joints ($1600) - Newer Rhino racks roof rack ($1200 installed) - Aftermarket cruise control  Plus a bunch of other stuff - too much to list into this vehicle  Body has about 280k miles. Lift, bumpers, rebuilt birfs, wheels, etc have much less obviously. Swap has about 630 miles since picked up from The Land Cruiser Shop.  If you have questions, want to share with a friend, or pick up, you can message me directly. I will review and if there are pertinent things that I am missing from the listing, I will update as needed.  A Google Drive link with many more pictures and some videos is available for interested parties.

Selling my V8 E39. Montreal Metallic Blue. These are generally considered to be some of the best cars BMW has ever made, and they're quickly becoming classics. 110k original miles. Mechanically the car is as close to perfect as you could ask for. It has not been neglected, and I have extensive service documents including the original build sheet. Runs and drives beautifully, everything works. The paint on the hood and roof is faded.  Lots of significant maintenance done in the last few years, including timing chain guides and tensioners which is a big deal on these cars. Suspension has been completely went over and replaced. Newer tires. Oil and transmission fluid changed. Cooling system overhaul a couple years ago. Does not leak or consume any fluids.  I'm selling because I am moving and cannot take it with me. This is a wonderful car that I wouldn't hesitate to drive anywhere. Clear title in my name.  show contact info  Calls or texts welcome.

1981 Jeep J10 Laredo Shortbed Pickup:  360 V8, auto trans, power steering, A/C, power windows, power locks, cruise control, BDS 4 inch lift with new shocks.  This truck spent its whole life in Flagstaff.  The bed has some rust but the cab is solid.  This is a project than runs and drives but should be trailered home.  I bought it with a bad transmission that I replaced with a used one from a buddies CJ7.  Then realized the freeze plugs were blown so pulled the motor to replace those.  The heater core froze too so it is currently bypassed.  The engine runs good and idles smooth but has excessive crankshaft endplay which causes the torque converter bolts to scrape the engine backing plate which makes a lot of noise.  I have the original fenders and hood but they are really rough.  Plan was to do a flatbed and LS conversion but plans change.  Great project for the FSJ or Wagoneer enthusiast.  $3000 firm

The Pontiac Fiero is a mid-engine sports car that was built by American automobile manufacturer General Motors from 1983 to 1988. The Fiero was designed by George Milidrag and Hulki Aldikacti as a sports car. It was the first two-seater Pontiac since the 1926 to 1938 coupes, and the first mass-produced mid-engine sports car by an American manufacturer. Many technologies incorporated in the Fiero design, such as composite panels, were radical for their time. Other features included hidden headlamps and, initially, integrated stereo speakers in the driver and passenger headrests. Car is in good running condition. Exterior paint is faded but good. Interior is good but needs some cosmetic restoration. Truly an American classic to own and hard to find with such low mileage. If you haven't driven one read this article: https://www.outmotorsports.com/2020/06/1986-pontiac-fiero-se-v6-the-hero-we-didnt-deserve/ Serious inquiries only
